ITV.Tour.de.France.2014.Stage.13.Highlights.PDTV.x264-NX

Friday 18th July 2014 ITV4
7pm to 8pm Highlights

Stage 13 highlights - the first of the real mountain stages of this year's Tour, the last 50km of this 197km stage will prove key in the battle for the overall title. The category one Col de Palaquit is 14km of fluctuating gradients, a hard climb that will split up the peloton before the final climb up Chamrousse. Presented by Gary Imlach with analysis from Chris Boardman, commentary by Phil Liggett and Paul Sherwen with Ned Boulting the reporter at the roadside.
